  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p><em><strong>Hunter Technique:</strong> 15th level</em></p>\n<p>You gain one of the following features of your choice.</p>\n<h3>Evasion</h3>\n<p>When you are subjected to an effect that allows you to make a Dexterity saving throw to take only half damage, you instead take no damage if you succeed on a saving throw, and only half damage if you fail.</p>\n<h3>Stand Against the Tide</h3>\n<p>When a hostile creature misses you with a melee attack, you can use your reaction to force that creature to repeat the same attack against another creature (other than itself) of your choice.</p>\n<h3>Uncanny Dodge</h3>\n<p>When an attacker that you can see hits you with an attack, you can use your reaction to halve the attack's damage against you.</p>",
